organization.description: The State of Alaska contributes several collections of digital geospatial data and services for government and public use. The Dept of Geological and Geophysical Surveys and the Dept of Natural Resources publish data to data.gov. The University of Alaska also operates the AlaskaMapped and GINA repositories of data.

name: 40ar-39ar-ages-from-the-tyonek-d-6-quadrangle-and-parts-of-tyonek-d-7-tyonek-d-5-and-tyonek-c-6
notes: 40Ar/39Ar data from plutonic and volcanic samples collected during preliminary mapping of the Tyonek D-6 and parts of Tyonek D-5, D-7 and C-6 quadrangles yield results indicating three discrete igneous events at about 55, 60 and 68 Ma. Igneous clasts from a boulder conglomerate retain Early Cretaceous ages.
